The paper describes the participation of a team in the SemEval 2016 challenge for sentiment analysis in Twitter. The approach involves generating and validating diverse feature sets for sentiment evaluation and optimizing evaluation measures using different learning strategies. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
